ing: 2 (15.5 ounce) cans garbanzo beans, drained and rinsed
des: "This is a typical Northern Indian recipe that is easy to make, and delicious.  You will need to go to an Indian grocery to buy the masalas."
ins: Heat oil in a saucepan over medium-high heat.  Stir in the garlic, onion, and ginger, and cook until browned.  Stir in the garam masala, channa masala spice, tomato, water, and garbanzos; season to taste with salt.  Bring to a simmer, the reduce heat to low, cover and simmer until garbanzos are very soft, about 20 minutes.
